In the mean field approximation which becomes exact at large $D$ 
we disregard fluctuations
of  $\lambda^{ab}$ and $\rho_{ab}$ about the  saddle-point values
${\bar\lambda}^{ab}$ and ${\bar\rho}_{ab} $,
{{i.e.}\ } simply substitute them by the mean values, 
which are the minima of the effective action~{(\ref{{aux1}})}. Integration around the 
saddle-point values will produce corrections which are subleading in $1/D$.

For diagonal and constant 
${\bar\lambda}^{ab}$ and ${\bar\rho}_{ab} $  the explicit formula for the determinant is 
well-known and for $L\gg\beta$ we obtain
\footnote{The averaged over quantum fluctuations induced metric
 $\left\langle\partial_a X\cdot \partial _b X \right\rangle$ which equals ${\bar\rho}_{ab}$ at large $D$
depends in fact on $\omega_1$ near the boundaries, 
but this is not essential for $L\gg \beta$~\cite{AM15b}.}
\begin{eqnarray}
S_{\rm eff}&=&\frac{K_0}2 \left( {\bar\lambda}^{11}\frac{L^2}{\omega_L^2} +
{\bar\lambda}^{22}\frac{\beta^2}{\omega_\beta^2} +
2\sqrt{{\bar\rho}_{11}{\bar\rho}_{22}}  
-{\bar\lambda}^{11}{\bar\rho}_{11} -{\bar\lambda}^{22}{\bar\rho}_{22}
\right)  \omega_\beta \omega_L {\nonumber \\*} &&
 -\frac{\pi d}{6}\sqrt{\frac{{\bar\lambda}^{22}}{{\bar\lambda}^{11}}}
\frac{\omega_L}{\omega_\beta}-\frac{d\sqrt{{\bar\rho}_{11}{\bar\rho}_{22}}\,  \omega_\beta \omega_L}{2\sqrt{{\bar\lambda}^{11}{\bar\lambda}^{22}}}
 \Lambda^2.
\label{Sec}
\end{eqnarray}

The minimum of the effective action {(\ref{{Sec}})} is reached at
 \begin{eqnarray}
{\bar\rho}_{11}&=&\frac{L^2}{\omega_L^2}
\frac{\left(\beta^2-\frac{\beta_0^2}{2C}\right)}{\left(\beta^2-\frac{\beta_0^2}{C}\right)}
\frac{C}{2C-1},{\nonumber \\*}
{\bar\rho}_{22}&=&\frac{1}{\omega_\beta^2}\left(\beta^2-\frac{\beta_0^2}{2C}\right)
\frac{C}{2C-1},
\label{rhogen}
\end{eqnarray}

